cl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hgt</span> : <span class=\"fn\">t</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhdsWithin\">nhdsWithin</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">x₀</span>)</span> (<span class=\"fn\">g</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set.image\">''</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ContDiff/Defs.html#ContDiffWithinAt\">ContDiffWithinAt</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/FDeriv/Defs.html#fderivWithin\">fderivWithin</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">t</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span></span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span> <span class=\"fn\">x₀</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The most general lemma stating that `x ↦ fderivWithin 𝕜 (f x) t (g x)` is `C^n`\nat a point within a set.\nTo show that `x ↦ D_yf(x,y)g(x)` (taken within `t`) is `C^m` at `x₀` within `s`, we require that\n* `f` is `C^n` at `(x₀, g(x₀))` within `(s ∪ {x₀}) × t` for `n ≥ m+1`.\n* `g` is `C^m` at `x₀` within `s`;\n* Derivatives are unique at `g(x)` within `t` for `x` sufficiently close to `x₀` within `s ∪ {x₀}`;\n* `t` is a neighborhood of `g(x₀)` within `g '' s`; ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ContDiff/Comp.html#ContDiffWithinAt.fderivWithin''","kind":"theorem","line":585,"name":"ContDiffWithinAt.fderivWithin''","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ContDiff/Comp.le